(43, 2, 5, 42, 5, 5, 6, 'Whatsoever he saith unto you, do it', 'Obedience to Instruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to divine instruction. In both passages, characters respond to a directive—Mary instructs the servants to follow Jesus'' words, and Simon Peter decides to let down the nets at Jesus'' command.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
