(43, 2, 6, 49, 5, 26, 26, NULL, 'Connection of Cleansing and Water', 'This connection highlights the theme of cleansing through water. In John 2:6, the waterpots are used for purification, while Ephesians 5:26 speaks of cleansing with ''washing of water.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 6, 58, 9, 10, 10, 'the purifying of the Jews', 'Purification and Rituals Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of purification rituals. John 2:6 mentions waterpots for Jewish purification, while Hebrews 9:10 discusses divers washings as part of carnal ordinances.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 6, 41, 7, 2, 5, 'purifying of the Jews', 'Purification and Tradition', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of ritual purification practices among the Jews. John mentions the waterpots used for purification, while Mark discusses the traditions of washing hands and vessels, highlighting the cultural importance of cleanliness in Jewish law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 6, 58, 6, 2, 2, 'purifying of the Jews', 'Purification and Baptism Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification found in both passages. John 2:6 mentions waterpots used for Jewish purification, while Hebrews 6:2 refers to the doctrine of baptisms, linking the concepts of ritual cleansing and spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 12, 4, 2, 6, 'filled them up to the brim', 'Miraculous Provision of Vessels', 'Both passages emphasize the act of filling vessels, leading to miraculous provision. In John, water is filled to the brim, while in 2 Kings, empty vessels are filled with oil. This connection highlights the theme of divine abundance through seemingly ordinary means.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 43, 2, 5, 5, NULL, 'Obedience to Jesus'' Commands', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to Jesus'' instructions. In John 2:5, Mary instructs the servants to do whatever Jesus says, which is exemplified in John 2:7 when they fill the waterpots as commanded.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 11, 17, 13, 13, 'Fill the waterpots with water', 'Provision and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience leading to divine provision. In both passages, individuals are instructed to act in faith—filling the waterpots and preparing food—before receiving God''s miraculous provision.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 41, 11, 2, 6, NULL, 'Obedience to Jesus'' Commands', 'This connection highlights the obedience of those following Jesus'' instructions. In both passages, individuals act according to Jesus'' commands, demonstrating faith in His authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 41, 14, 12, 17, 'waterpots with water', 'Water and Preparation Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparation involving water. In John 2:7, the act of filling waterpots signifies readiness, while in Mark 14:12-17, the disciples prepare for the Passover, following instructions related to a pitcher of water.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 6, 6, 3, 5, 'Fill the waterpots with water', 'Water and Obedience in Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to divine instruction. In both passages, the act of following God''s command leads to a significant outcome: filling the waterpots results in a miracle, while marching around Jericho leads to the city''s walls falling.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 7, 12, 5, 10, 14, 'Fill the waterpots with water', 'Water and Cleansing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of washing as a means of purification. In John, water is filled to the brim for a miraculous transformation, while in 2 Kings, washing in the Jordan leads to Naaman''s healing. This connection highlights the significance of water in the process of cleansing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 8, 20, 3, 5, 6, 'bear unto the governor of the feast', 'Trust and Obedience in Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of trust in divine guidance. In John 2:8, the servants obey the command to draw out the wine, reflecting the trust in the Lord emphasized in Proverbs 3:5-6.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 8, 43, 2, 9, 9, 'Draw out now, and bear', 'Connection of Actions in Miracle', 'This connection highlights the act of drawing out the water, which directly leads to the tasting of the wine by the governor of the feast. Both passages emphasize the role of the servants in the miracle, showcasing their knowledge of the transformation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 8, 45, 13, 7, 7, 'bear unto the governor of the feast', 'Connection of Duty and Honor', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling obligations to authorities. In John 2:8, the act of bearing the wine to the governor reflects the importance of honoring those in positions of authority, similar to Romans 13:7''s call to render honor to whom honor is due.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 8, 21, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Actions and Outcomes', 'This connection highlights the theme of actions leading to outcomes. In John 2:8, the act of drawing out the wine signifies a moment of transformation, while Ecclesiastes 9:6 reflects on the finality of human experiences and emotions, suggesting that actions ultimately lead to a cessation of influence.', 'theme', 0.293, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 9, 43, 4, 46, 46, NULL, 'Miracles in Cana of Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' miraculous acts in Cana of Galilee, first turning water into wine and later healing a nobleman''s son. This connection highlights the significance of Cana as a site of Jesus'' early miracles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 9, 43, 7, 17, 17, NULL, 'Understanding Through Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge gained through action. In John 2:9, the servants who acted by drawing the water knew the truth of the miracle, while in John 7:17, doing God''s will leads to understanding of doctrine.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 9, 19, 119, 100, 100, NULL, 'Understanding Through Experience', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding gained through experience. In John 2:9, the servants who drew the water had knowledge of the miracle, paralleling Psalms 119:100 where understanding is linked to keeping precepts.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 10, 66, 7, 16, 17, 'good wine until now', 'Connection of Abundance and Provision', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance and divine provision. In John 2:10, the good wine represents the best offerings, while Revelation 7:16-17 speaks of God providing for the needs of His people, ensuring they will not hunger or thirst.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 10, 20, 9, 1, 6, 'good wine', 'Connection of Wine and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of wine as a symbol of quality and wisdom. Both passages emphasize the idea of offering the best wine, with John noting that good wine is kept until later and Proverbs inviting the simple to partake of mingled wine, representing understanding.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 10, 42, 16, 25, 25, 'good wine', 'Contrast of Good and Evil', 'This connection highlights the contrast between good and bad experiences in life. In John 2:10, the good wine is kept until the end, while in Luke 16:25, the rich man received good things in life but faces torment afterward.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 2, 10, 1, 43, 34, 34, NULL, 'Celebration and Abundance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of abundance during feasting. In John 2:10, the good wine symbolizes the best being saved for last, while in Genesis 43:34, Benjamin receives a larger portion, highlighting special favor and joy in the meal.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
